		<name>Mage Slayer</name>
		<prerequisite/>
		<text>You have practiced techniques useful in melee combat against spellcasters, gaining the following benefits:</text>
		<text> </text>
		<text>• When a creature within 5 feet of you casts a spell, you can use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against that creature.</text>
		<text> </text>
		<text>• When you damage a creature that is concentrating on a spell, that creature has disadvantage on the saving throw it makes to maintain its concentration.</text>
		<text> </text>
		<text>• You have advantage on saving throws against spells cast by creatures within 5 feet of you.</text>
		<text></text>
		<text>Source: Player's Handbook, page 168</text>
	</feat>
	<feat>
		<name>Magic Initiate</name>
		<prerequisite/>
		<text>Choose a class: bard, cleric, druid, sorcerer, warlock, or wizard. You learn two cantrips of your choice from that class's spell list.</text>
		<text> </text>
		<text>In addition, choose one 1st-level spell from that same list. You learn that spell and can cast it at its lowest level. Once you cast it, you must finish a long rest before you can cast it again using this feat.</text>
		<text> </text>
		<text>Your spellcasting ability for these spells depends on the class you chose: Charisma for bard, sorcerer, or warlock; Wisdom for cleric or druid: or Intelligence for wizard.</text>
